MAMELODI Sundowns kept their hopes of a league and cup double alive after defeating Cape Town City 2-1 in their exciting Nedbank Cup quarter-final in Cape Town on Sunday.The Brazilians are now going to face Maritzburg United in the semi-finals of the Ke Yona Cup.Percy Tau and Hlompho Kekana long range in the space of eight minutes in the second half ensured Sundowns go into a deserved two-goal lead until the 69 munite where Bradley Ralani pulled one back for his side.Sundowns managed to hold on for the remainder of the game to go through to the next round where they will be visiting on form Fadlu Davids side, Maritzburg on the weekend of 21-22 April.Kaizer Chiefs who eliminated Baroka FC on Saturday night will play hosts to Bethlehem based outfit Free State Stars in the other semifinal.The Brazilians were forceful in attack in the early exchanges, holding the Citizens in their own half.Benni McCarthy’s charges were playing on the counter-attack and they looked dangerous whenever they went on the break as the Tshwane giants were playing a high line.Sundowns got their opening goal on the counter attack in the 54th minute when Tau converted Khama Billiat low shot to put his side on the lead.Kekana fired his shot from some 30 metres out in the 63rd minute to double the lead as City again gave away possession.Sundowns defence made an error but which allowed Ralani to get a shot in on goal‚ after the ball deflected on Ricardo Nascimento‚ it trickled past Denis Onyango.Taariq Fielies made a goal-line clearance in the 72nd minute to deny Tau his second goal for the Brazilians after beating goalkeeper Stephens.The match was tightly contested with 10 minutes left to play but time was running out for City to force the encounter into extra-time.Ayanda Patosi came close to finding a equaliser for the hosts three minutes before time with a header at the back post but he could not find the target as the Mother City club ran out of time and crashed out of the competition.SEMI FINAL